<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17640728-23">
               <interp inst="t17640728-23" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-23" type="year" value="1764"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-23" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17640728"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17640728-23" type="date" value="17640728"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17640728-23-off115-c157" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-23-defend212 t17640728-23-off115 t17640728-23-verdict117"></join>
         
               <p>419. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640728-23-defend212" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Caffry 
                  <interp inst="t17640728-23-defend212" type="surname" value="Caffry"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-defend212" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-defend212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17640728-23-off115" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-off115" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-off115" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing four pounds weight of bacon, value 2 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17640728-23-victim214" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Dodd 
                  <interp inst="t17640728-23-victim214" type="surname" value="Dodd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-victim214" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-victim214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-23-off115 t17640728-23-victim214"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17640728-23-cd116" type="crimeDate">June 11</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-23-off115 t17640728-23-cd116"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640728-23-person215">
                  Peter 
                  Dodd 
               <interp inst="t17640728-23-person215" type="surname" value="Dodd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person215" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am journeyman to my brother, Mr. 
               <persName id="t17640728-23-person216">
                  John 
                  Dodd 
               <interp inst="t17640728-23-person216" type="surname" value="Dodd"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person216" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person216" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 11th of June last, I happened to go from behind the counter, in our shop, in Newgate-street: a gentleman said a man had taken a piece of bacon; I went out and followed the prisoner, and saw the piece of bacon in his hand, by the side of him; I asked him where he was going with the bacon? he said, no where, but a man had given it him; my brother charged a constable with him, and he was sent to the Compter. It was taken out of the window; I had cut it about a quarter of an hour before: (Produced and deposed to). He was very much in liquor.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176407280011"></xptr>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>As I was coming along, there was a great mob about Mr. Dodd's house: what they intended to do, I do not know. I don't know any thing about the bacon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17640728-23-person217">
                  Michael 
                  White 
               <interp inst="t17640728-23-person217" type="surname" value="White"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person217" type="given" value="Michael"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-person217" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I have known the prisoner about four months: it was Whitsun-Monday, and he had been drunk that day. As to the fact, I know nothing of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17640728-23-verdict117" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-verdict117" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-verdict117" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty, 10 d.
            </rs> 
                  <rs id="t17640728-23-punish118" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-punish118" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640728-23-punish118" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640728-23-defend212 t17640728-23-punish118"></join>
               W
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
